==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: narrate
<hw>nar*rate"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Narrated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Narrating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>narratus</ets>, p. p.
of <ets>narrare</ets> to narrate, prob. for <ets>gnarigare</ets>, fr.
<ets>gnarus</ets> knowing. See <er>Ignore</er>, <er>Know</er>.]</ety>
<def>To tell, rehearse, or recite, as a story; to relate the particulars
of; to go through with in detail, as an incident or transaction; to give
an account of.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To relate; recount; detail; describe.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>narration</ent>⟦br⟧
